contentrichtext.text: {{wiktionary|ESD}} '''ESD''' may mean: *[[Ecologically sustainable development]] *[[Educational service district (disambiguation)]], various state-level legislative groupings for schools in some US states. *[[Electronic services delivery]], government services provided through the Internet or other electronic means *[[Electronic software delivery]], Distribution of software by digital transfer rather than by physical media. *[[Electrostatic discharge]], a sudden and momentary electric current that flows between two objects *[[Electrostatic dissipative]], static dissipative material that will allow the transfer of charge to ground or other conductive object *[[Electrostatic sensitive device]], any component (primarily electrical) which can be damaged by common static charges *[[Elmstead Woods railway station]], in Elmstead in the London Borough of Bromley *[[Emergency shut down]], a valve that stops flow in an emergency *[[End-systolic dimension]], the diameter across a ventricle in the heart *[[Endoscopic submucosal dissection]], a medical therapy with [[endoscopy]] *[[Energy spectral density]], a part of a function in statistical signal processing *[[Engineering Society of Detroit]], a multi-disciplinary association in south-east Michigan *[[Enlightened Sound Daemon]], is the sound server for Enlightenment and GNOME. *[[Environmental secondary detector]], a gaseous detection device used with environmental scanning electron microscopes *[[Extreme subdwarf]], a star with lower luminosity than that of a main-sequence star of the same spectral type *The [[International_Air_Transport_Association_airport_code|IATA]] airport code for [[Orcas Island Airport]] '''Advertising Terminology:''' *English Speaking Developed Nations - Often used in the context of ad campaign targeting for USA, CA, UK, IE, AU, and NZ {{disambig}}
